result.name: Kind Kitchen by Green Common

reviews.text:
Green Common is always my to go place when I want to purchase some healthy vegan or vegetarian food. I feel good shopping in Green Common as they promote a conscious consuming habits, such as being eco-friendly, as well as going green to be nice to environment and animals.

Kind Kitchen operates with this core elements - be kind to animals when you eat. There are many reasons to go green, and stopping animal cruelty could be one of them. Kind Kitchen offers a nice alternative to meat with its plant-based substitutes, such as Beyond Meat from USA and OmiPork. I am a fans of Beyond Meat, as it tastes so much like real beef, yet it’s harmless to animals and environment, and healthier than ordinary beef with less cholesterol and more dietary fibers. 

This Deluxe Burger I ordered is massive! I love the Beyond Meat patty so much! It’s so juicy and flavoured. Seriously, I can’t tell how different it is from real beef patty. The truffle sauce is gorgeous and goes so well with the burger. I wish there were more so that I can dip the fries in it. Also, the bits and pieces of mushroom top up the whole burger quite a lot.

The fries were freshly fried, hot and crispy. Yum Yum!

Kind Kitchen is an okay effort from the Green Common team to upscale its usual offerings. 

The menu is quite impressive in its offerings, but don’t expect to be blown away by the taste of anything. We’ve been here a few times now, and most dishes have been disappointing.

We took advantage of the Thankful Week offer (50% off Beyond Meat menu items) and had a nice meal. We’d tried the Deluxe Beyond Truffle Burger before and knew to avoid that - it’s quite literally just a Beyond patty with a dollop of truffle sauce on top, so nothing mind blowing. We went for the double Beyond cheeseburger, which was tasty.

Service was poor. We struggled to get anyone’s attention for long periods and was never able to order from our table; we always had to approach a staff member and ask to order. 

The worst part of this is that after we’d finished our burgers and ordered coffee (which is great by the way), no one came to clear our table. Even when they brought our coffee to us and saw our empty plates, nothing was cleared. When you’re paying a 10% service charge, you expect some actual service.

Overall, an okay experience and the menu gives you the opportunity to try a range of mock meat/dairy products that are quickly making a vegan diet more accessible to the masses. 

But the standard Green Common restaurants offer nearly just as much for a lot less. Our bill would have been a difficult-to-swallow $450 without the Thankful Week 50% off; instead we paid $270, which seemed more appropriate for the quality.

One of my favorite and go-to lunch spots when I feel like vegetarian food. Never got tired of their food as there is a good variety of international dishes that got transformed into their vegetarian version while deliciousness is preserved. 
Would highly recommend their ramen in soy soup, curry rice with Omni pork hamburger steak, and hamburgers. Lunch set starts from $108.
Best bet for a Vegan meal. Quality was good, but last visit saw standards dropping
Amazing omnipork sphagetti and also dumplings meals. A fantastic place to eat 👍

result.name: YUM CHA (Central)

reviews.text: If you are looking for traditional dim sum. I wouldn’t recommend this place. It’s more fusion and creative dim sum, which has its charm but may not be my cup of tea. The interior design is really nice. Probably a good place to have dinner with colleagues.

We just had dessert here and the food was excellent (the pineapple puff birds are adorable and the specialty buns are too cute). Highly recommend for some great pics! HOWEVER. The service was really bad. They forgot our drinks and the waiters kept ignoring us for about 45 minutes. Much of the wait staff was also very rude. Most alarming was seeing the manager (I think he was the manager, he was wearing a button down instead of the t-shirt everyone else on) PUNCH a waiter THREE TIMES in the face for some reason. This was out in the open in front of the whole restaurant (though it would be unacceptable anywhere). That was honestly insane...

Great food but confused service!

This place is for the gram! The food presentation is great and everything was quite tasty. The majority of our dishes were well done but we did over order, unbeknown to us at the time.

Admittedly the waitress serving us had a trainee tag on, but there were two things missing in the service which was irritating.

1. She didn’t greet or speak at all. She was quiet as a mouse to the point where when we asked her something she walked off on us without acknowledging whether she understood what we wanted. 

2. She knew the table size and as the menu doesn’t show pics of what a quantity looks like. She should have guided us on what and how much to order.
What’s not to like about this fun restaurant? It’s cute AND tasty. Look at this poor little red bean bun... aaaahh!

Fun ambiance. Adorable dim sum but the food itself is under par. Quite mediocre. But you go there for the creativity in the food design and less for the taste. Great place to bring out of Townes visiting Hong Kong. Conveniently located in central, a hop skip and jump away from many hotels in the area and IFC mall.
